+Etymological+Dictionary&amp;rft.atitle=Slang&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.etymonline.com%2Findex.php%3Fterm%3Dslang&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASlang" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li> <li id="cite_note-Dumas&amp;Lighter-4"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Dumas&amp;Lighter_4-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Dumas&amp;Lighter_4-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation journal">Dumas, Bethany K.; Lighter, Jonathan (1978). "Is Slang a Word for Linguists?". <i>American Speech</i>. <b>53</b> (5): 14–15. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//doi.org/10.2307%2F455336">10.2307/455336</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=American+Speech&amp;rft.atitle=Is+Slang+a+Word+for+Linguists%3F&amp;rft.volume=53&amp;rft.issue=5&amp;rft.pages=14-15&amp;rft.date=1978&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.2307%2F455336&amp;rft.aulast=Dumas&amp;rft.aufirst=Bethany+K.&amp;rft.au=Lighter%2C+Jonathan&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASlang" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li> <li id="cite_note-People's_Poetry-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-People's_Poetry_5-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation book">Adams, Michael (2009). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://site.ebrary.com/lib/berkeley/docDetail.action?docID=10597107"><i>Slang: The People's Poetry</i></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Slang%3A+The+People%27s+Poetry&amp;rft.date=2009&amp;rft.aulast=Adams&amp;rft.aufirst=Michael&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fsite.ebrary.com%2Flib%2Fberkeley%2FdocDetail.action%3F